    <note id="note-00002">
    <title>Using boolean variables</title>
    <para id="para-00005">A boolean variable already has a value of True or False and can be used directly in a condition rather than using the equality operator. Ex: <code class="python inline-code" lang="python">if is_raining == True:</code> can be simplified to <code class="python inline-code" lang="python">if is_raining:</code>.</para>
    </note>
