    <section id="sect-00003">
    <title>if-else statement</title>
    <para id="para-00011">An if statement defines actions to be performed when a condition is true. What if an action needs to be performed only when the condition is false? Ex: If the restaurant is less than a mile away, we'll walk. Else, we'll drive.</para>
    <para id="para-00012">An <term id="term-00003">else statement</term> is used with an if statement and contains a body of statements that is executed when the if statement's condition is False. When an if-else statement is executed, one and only one of the branches is taken. That is, the body of the if or the body of the else is executed. Note: The else statement is at the same level of indentation as the if statement, and the body is indented.</para>
    <para id="para-00020">if-else statement template</para>
    <code class="python line-numbering" lang="python">
    # Statements before

    if condition:
      # Body
    else:
      # Body
    
    # Statements after
    </code>
