    <note class="practice-program" id="note-00007">
    <title>Converting temperature units</title>
    <para id="para-00017">The following program reads in a temperature as a float and the unit as a string: "f" for Fahrenheit or "c" for Celsius.</para><para id="para-00018">Calculate new_temp, the result of converting temp from Fahrenheit to Celsius or Celsius to Fahrenheit based on unit. Calculate new_unit: "c" if unit is "f" and "f" if unit is "c".</para>
    <para id="para-00019">Conversion formulas:
    <list id="list-00002">
    <item>degrees Celsius = (degrees Fahrenheit - 32) * 5/9</item>
    <item>degrees Fahrenheit = (degrees Celsius * 5/9) + 32</item>
    </list></para>
